{
  "stem": "26111.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I never wore-- no, that was not-- that regulation didn't come into force until after the war, or just before the war started.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think after the war-- after the war started-- I'm sorry, no, not after the war.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "After the war started, which was September, less than a year later-- September-- 2nd of September, '39.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I never wore the star.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I, I had-- I suddenly remember the time that I got my passport.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was a children's passport, a one-page thing, not the-- not the book-type passport that we know that adults got.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I got a, a children's pass, as they called them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it had my photo on it and the vital-- the vital statistics.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I was 14 at the time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I think you're considered legally a child until you're 16.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it had a big J stamped over and on top of it, so that-- And with that, armed with that, one suitcase, and the limit, which was 10 marks-- 10, 10 Reichsmarks-- not deutsche marks, that was before the currency reform, which came after the war-- I set off for England.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But that's the next part of the story.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I was already-- at that time, my father had apparently already made the first-- taken the first steps toward my, my emigration.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I actually had to go to several, several offices.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember going to the Swedish Embassy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was some talk about sending me to Sweden rather than England.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was apparently still possible.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "A friend of mine was, was indeed sent to Sweden, even though his parents came to England in-- sometime in '39, before the war started.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I went and spent a lot of time in the-- on these formalities, like the passport.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
